				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$Doubling\, time (hours)=\frac{48 hours\times ln(2)}{ln(\frac{{N}_{f}}{{N}_{i}})}$$\end{document}Doublingtime(hours)=48hours×ln(2)ln(NfNi)where 48 h indicates the cell culture duration, Nf indicates the final number of viable cells at the endpoint and Ni indicates the initial seeding density.
